The insurance company will replace your vehicle with a new vehicle of the same make, model, and features after a total loss if:

• your vehicle is a total loss;
• you purchased it new (or as a demonstrator model) from the manufacturer or their dealer;
• where your vehicle is financed, your financier has given us written consent; and
• your vehicle is less than three years old from when it was first registered at the time it is declared a total loss.

According to the context information, if a new replacement vehicle is not available, the policyholder has several options for compensation, including:

1. Repairing their vehicle;
2. Paying the reasonable cost of repairing their vehicle;
3. Paying the market value of their vehicle when the policy schedule shows that their vehicle is insured for market value;
4. Paying the agreed value of their vehicle when the policy schedule shows that their vehicle is insured for an agreed value.

